Python: 3.8+

Library: Pillow
 (pip install pillow)

OS: Windows/macOS/Linux (paths default to a Windows OneDrive folder, but can be overridden via CLI)

  Key Capabilities

Recursive ingestion of common image formats: .bmp, .jpeg, .jpg, .png, .tif, .tiff, .webp.

Color-safe I/O:

PNG (RGBA/LA) → composited onto a white RGB canvas.

JPEG writes forced to RGB (no accidental CMYK/RGBA saves).

Deterministic augmentations (8 variants per image):

Horizontal flip, vertical flip

Rotate 90°, rotate 270°

Brightness ×1.50, contrast ×1.50, sharpness ×1.50

Blur (Pillow’s ImageFilter.BLUR)

File-type preservation: writes augmented files using the same extension as the source (with format-appropriate encoder options—e.g., JPEG quality=95 + optimize).

Safe default outputs: Originals are copied (optional), augments saved alongside them in the derived output tree. 

augment_ds

  INSTALLATION
  python -m venv .venv
# Windows
.venv\Scripts\activate
# macOS/Linux
source .venv/bin/activate

pip install pillow
